Zac!

18:37.925 --> 18:40.019
- Get in. I'll drive.
- No!

18:40.039 --> 18:42.059
Zac, let him drive!

18:55.148 --> 18:57.114
Why did my father send you?

18:57.234 --> 18:59.044
Why do you think?

19:00.224 --> 19:02.108
I told him to send help,

19:02.127 --> 19:03.956
not you and your boyfriend.

19:04.432 --> 19:05.922
He's saving your life, Zac.

19:05.950 --> 19:07.211
Is that what you call it?

19:07.212 --> 19:09.306
He practically served me
up to Al-Harazi on a plate,

19:09.306 --> 19:10.221
and Ayoob is dead.

19:10.258 --> 19:11.574
His friend betrayed all of us.

19:11.593 --> 19:13.953
It doesn't change it!

19:14.073 --> 19:16.287
You've only made things
worse. Where are you taking me?

19:16.407 --> 19:17.831
Across the border. To Morocco.

19:17.858 --> 19:19.386
I have to make a stop first.

19:19.506 --> 19:20.710
What for?

19:20.978 --> 19:22.779
Does it matter? You work for me.

19:25.524 --> 19:26.483
Frank?

19:26.529 --> 19:27.773
What are you doing?

19:31.021 --> 19:32.767
It's your call.

19:37.260 --> 19:38.709
Where is this stop?

19:38.829 --> 19:40.871
It's 20 minutes that way.

19:42.343 --> 19:44.639
You're a pain in the ass, you know that?

19:46.514 --> 19:47.859
I know.

20:28.711 --> 20:30.928
This is where you went hiding?

20:30.973 --> 20:33.672
The Bedouins have no love for Al-Harazi.

20:33.792 --> 20:36.416
The enemy of my enemy is my friend...

20:36.636 --> 20:39.298
Yeah, that and payback for some radios

20:39.326 --> 20:40.743
I funnelled them a few months ago.

20:40.863 --> 20:42.454
Smart investment.

20:42.574 --> 20:45.124
One of the few worthwhile
things I learned from my father.

20:45.124 --> 20:46.487
Just this way...

20:59.374 --> 21:01.002
You gone long time.

21:01.041 --> 21:03.554
"You were gone a long time."

21:05.265 --> 21:06.728
This is Ali.

21:06.746 --> 21:07.795
My right hand.

21:07.915 --> 21:09.820
I see. And Ali's coming with us?

21:09.856 --> 21:10.954
No.

21:11.182 --> 21:12.262
They all are.

21:15.711 --> 21:18.355
- Nineteen boys.
- Is that a problem?

21:18.382 --> 21:20.120
Getting them past al-Hazari?

21:21.071 --> 21:24.044
That's more than a problem.
It's practically impossible.

21:29.807 --> 21:31.920
I understand the difficulty.

21:32.171 --> 21:33.328
I do.

21:34.240 --> 21:35.807
But if I leave these boys behind,

21:35.835 --> 21:37.600
he will kill each and every one of them,

21:37.609 --> 21:38.990
just to punish me.

21:39.713 --> 21:41.798
I can't let that happen.

21:43.015 --> 21:44.871
You can't.

21:58.352 --> 21:59.931
What are we going to do?

22:00.333 --> 22:03.090
I have no bloody idea.

22:04.570 --> 22:07.013
I don't know what to say, I'm...

22:08.206 --> 22:09.419
Sorry.

22:10.643 --> 22:12.172
You didn't know this would happen.

22:12.209 --> 22:13.334
I should have.

22:14.547 --> 22:17.139
The job has spun out of control.

22:18.516 --> 22:21.163
And I know you only took it because of me.

22:31.462 --> 22:33.400
- How do that?
- Do what?

22:33.520 --> 22:34.698
Ali...

22:34.818 --> 22:37.682
My father sent Frank and
Cat to get us out of here.

22:37.802 --> 22:39.263
You're gonna help them.

22:39.281 --> 22:40.964
This is all he send?

22:41.706 --> 22:42.729
Yeah.

22:42.730 --> 22:44.477
We screwed.

22:44.597 --> 22:46.050
I like this kid.

22:46.736 --> 22:48.131
You know what a map is?

22:48.332 --> 22:49.672
I'm gonna need one.

22:55.077 --> 22:57.684
- You don't look well.
- I'm alright.

22:58.150 --> 22:59.888
How did you get that?

23:01.059 --> 23:03.437
They shot at the bus to stop it.

23:03.483 --> 23:05.138
If they'd checked the luggage compartment,

23:05.181 --> 23:06.784
I'd be dead right now.

23:07.717 --> 23:09.931
I'm impressed you got the boys away.

23:11.833 --> 23:13.342
Ayoob did,

23:13.717 --> 23:15.547
with help from the Bedouins.

23:16.041 --> 23:18.126
Al-Harazi said he'd
kill one of them each day

23:18.161 --> 23:19.694
unless I surrendered.

23:20.074 --> 23:21.830
He told us you're a thief.

23:22.265 --> 23:23.579
He would say that.

23:23.699 --> 23:25.114
What do you mean?

23:26.788 --> 23:28.919
When I came here two years ago,

23:28.937 --> 23:30.822
al-Harazi was happy.

23:31.727 --> 23:34.617
Not because I provided shelter
for two dozen homeless boys,

23:34.626 --> 23:36.025
but because it meant aid

23:36.044 --> 23:37.579
flowing to Zouerat.

23:37.937 --> 23:40.581
Aid he could skim and sell off.

23:40.837 --> 23:43.233
That's part of the game. You know that.

23:44.552 --> 23:46.426
He's a parasite,

23:47.011 --> 23:48.877
making money off other people's money,

23:48.891 --> 23:50.405
he's like my father.

23:50.624 --> 23:53.195
He got greedy and my kids got hungry.

23:53.441 --> 23:56.495
Please tell me you didn't
steal food back from him?

23:56.541 --> 23:57.931
Some of it.

23:58.299 --> 23:59.633
What else could I do?

23:59.753 --> 24:01.928
You put their lives at risk, Zac.

24:04.243 --> 24:06.740
This is happening because of you.

24:07.481 --> 24:09.767
It's because of me they're alive at all.

24:10.910 --> 24:13.590
It's because of you that
they're gonna to stay that way.

24:16.150 --> 24:17.523
Excuse me.

24:27.657 --> 24:29.228
Frank!

24:33.934 --> 24:35.331
Let's get him inside.

24:36.804 --> 24:38.218
It's infected.

24:38.514 --> 24:39.586
How bad?

24:39.940 --> 24:41.212
Bad.

24:42.910 --> 24:44.989
He may have blood poisoning.

24:46.361 --> 24:49.681
Stupid man, he takes care
of everybody but himself.

24:50.220 --> 24:52.632
I'm OK. I'm fine.

24:55.888 --> 24:57.656
He's not going anywhere.

25:04.160 --> 25:06.364
It's 10 kilometers to the Moroccan border

25:06.401 --> 25:07.901
if we take this road.

25:09.769 --> 25:11.523
You know that border is disputed?

25:11.643 --> 25:14.011
Separated by two
kilometers of no man's land,

25:14.020 --> 25:16.422
littered with land mines
to discourage refugees.

25:16.443 --> 25:18.337
I'm hoping we can use
that to our advantage.

25:18.457 --> 25:21.036
Even if you can, how do you
fit 19 kids on that truck?

25:21.156 --> 25:23.681
I know where there is bus,
big enough for everyone.

25:23.949 --> 25:25.628
Yes Ali, we know your bus.

25:25.650 --> 25:27.318
It's got a shot radiator.

25:27.438 --> 25:29.969
I could probably fix it
with a hose from the truck.

25:30.089 --> 25:32.341
See? We already work together.

25:32.387 --> 25:33.539
What about Zac?

25:34.793 --> 25:36.630
He won't make it without medicine.

25:38.030 --> 25:40.251
Clinic in Zouaret. It has medicine.

25:40.371 --> 25:41.523
That doctor won't help.

25:41.533 --> 25:43.266
- Then I steal.
- You steal?

25:43.279 --> 25:45.080
I'm not scared. I'm a sneaky bastard.

25:45.117 --> 25:46.617
That's what Zac says.

25:48.272 --> 25:50.010
OK, but it sounds pretty risky,

25:50.037 --> 25:51.308
even for a sneaky bastard.

25:51.354 --> 25:52.209
I'll go.

25:52.443 --> 25:53.851
Look at your face.

25:53.971 --> 25:55.250
Look at my face.

25:55.370 --> 25:58.625
Which face has a better chance
not getting killed in Zouaret?

26:01.753 --> 26:04.570
Seems like you're a
persuasive bastard, too.

26:05.539 --> 26:06.504
OK,

26:06.624 --> 26:08.127
then you look through the boxes

26:08.158 --> 26:09.273
and take anything

26:09.393 --> 26:11.630
that ends with "illin."

26:13.715 --> 26:14.785
OK?

26:14.822 --> 26:15.865
Ampicillin...

26:15.901 --> 26:17.090
Oxicillin...

26:17.210 --> 26:18.188
Got it ?

26:18.947 --> 26:20.630
And take syringes,

26:20.630 --> 26:22.002
needles, for shots.

26:22.038 --> 26:23.538
I don't like needles.

26:23.575 --> 26:25.374
Neither do I, tough guy.

26:25.742 --> 26:27.517
Can you get the Bedouins to help take Zac

26:27.518 --> 26:28.743
and the boys to the bus?

26:28.863 --> 26:29.912
We'll meet you there.

26:30.313 --> 26:31.991
We really shouldn't move him.

26:32.282 --> 26:33.966
We don't have a choice.

26:48.692 --> 26:49.881
Your friend,

26:49.899 --> 26:51.555
Zac like her.

26:52.935 --> 26:54.883
- You think?
- Too much.

26:55.917 --> 26:57.234
He go with her,

26:57.279 --> 26:58.798
he not stay with us.

27:00.076 --> 27:01.890
How did you meet Zac?

27:03.079 --> 27:04.745
He caught me stealing shoes.

27:04.947 --> 27:06.710
I think he going to hit me.

27:06.830 --> 27:09.005
Instead he give me job at school.

27:10.453 --> 27:12.079
Why were you stealing shoes?

27:12.199 --> 27:13.780
Shoes bring money.

27:13.822 --> 27:15.326
I was hungry.

27:15.363 --> 27:17.713
- Where are your parents?
- Dead.

27:18.694 --> 27:20.366
That's why I come Zouaret.

27:21.029 --> 27:23.109
Zac give me home...

27:23.886 --> 27:24.846
Help...

27:24.966 --> 27:26.210
Not just me.

27:26.330 --> 27:27.755
All people.

27:28.169 --> 27:30.099
We call him Melak Zouaret.

27:30.105 --> 27:31.771
You know what is "melak"?

27:32.932 --> 27:34.039
Angel.

27:35.383 --> 27:37.633
Zac Angel of Zouaret.

27:41.100 --> 27:42.527
Maybe you...

27:42.867 --> 27:44.228
melak too.

27:44.969 --> 27:47.274
Sorry, Ali. I'm nobody's angel.

27:55.523 --> 27:56.779
Where are we going?

27:56.980 --> 27:58.176
To the bus.

27:58.752 --> 28:01.998
- I can't, not without the kids.
- They're coming.

28:04.019 --> 28:04.868
Wait.

28:04.988 --> 28:05.788
What?

28:05.908 --> 28:07.312
Your bracelet...

28:07.432 --> 28:09.049
Should be in your pocket.

28:12.570 --> 28:13.960
I still don't understand

28:13.997 --> 28:15.872
how you got mixed up in all this, Cat.

28:15.992 --> 28:17.700
Your father called for advice.

28:17.729 --> 28:19.068
As it happens,

28:19.188 --> 28:20.893
I work for Frank now.

28:21.588 --> 28:23.161
He's good, huh?

28:24.359 --> 28:26.052
He's the best.

28:31.055 --> 28:33.808
We work together. That's all.

28:37.531 --> 28:38.976
- Are you OK?
- Yeah...

28:38.988 --> 28:40.567
I'm fine.

28:42.734 --> 28:45.625
You know I still care about you, Cat.

28:46.823 --> 28:48.597
Don't start this, Zac

28:48.615 --> 28:50.362
You kept the bracelet all these years.

28:50.398 --> 28:51.844
It must've meant something.

28:53.621 --> 28:55.439
It means I like jewelry.

29:00.008 --> 29:01.292
Where's Ali?

29:01.337 --> 29:04.245
He's with Frank. They went
to steal you some antibiotics.

29:04.546 --> 29:05.545
No.

29:05.880 --> 29:06.797
What?

29:06.834 --> 29:09.239
He told you he's a
sneaky bastard, didn't he?

29:11.334 --> 29:13.996
He's the worst thief on the planet.

29:24.198 --> 29:25.694
Here, take this.

29:30.294 --> 29:33.633
You get in trouble, you
shout as loud as you can, OK?

31:41.177 --> 31:42.777
_

32:14.791 --> 32:16.419
_

32:16.431 --> 32:18.861
Not so sneaky, Ali.

32:24.248 --> 32:26.498
_

32:26.507 --> 32:27.833
_

32:27.861 --> 32:29.690
_

32:29.810 --> 32:32.013
- Pardon me.
- _

32:32.013 --> 32:34.126
Pick on someone your own size.

32:42.390 --> 32:44.324
Where is the kafir?

32:52.599 --> 32:54.367
You're a funny guy, huh?

32:54.605 --> 32:56.800
You want to die for your friend?

32:57.371 --> 32:58.986
He's not my friend.

33:00.129 --> 33:01.174
So...

33:01.375 --> 33:03.467
this is a rescue mission?

33:04.437 --> 33:06.623
You should have brought more men.

33:07.046 --> 33:09.539
I get that a lot.

33:09.548 --> 33:10.984
Stop!

33:19.125 --> 33:20.760
You were a soldier,

33:21.094 --> 33:22.792
I can tell.

33:23.973 --> 33:26.387
Your training made you hard to break.

33:28.401 --> 33:30.476
Let's see how hard.

33:38.377 --> 33:39.796
At three,

33:40.012 --> 33:41.817
I cut his throat.

33:43.326 --> 33:44.607
One...

33:45.250 --> 33:46.482
Don't say!

33:46.718 --> 33:47.735
Two!

33:50.616 --> 33:51.723
Don't!

33:52.080 --> 33:54.375
He's at the oasis with the other boys.

33:54.385 --> 33:55.409
No!

33:58.397 --> 34:00.659
See, it wasn't so hard.

34:12.877 --> 34:14.268
Run!

34:40.328 --> 34:41.882
We're locked in!

34:44.806 --> 34:46.054
Push!

35:10.557 --> 35:13.355
You are sneaky bastard too!

35:37.492 --> 35:38.516
You OK?

35:40.129 --> 35:41.626
I've been better.

35:42.731 --> 35:44.589
Give Cat the medicine.

35:46.062 --> 35:47.452
Good boy!

36:00.404 --> 36:01.410
Ouch.

36:01.530 --> 36:02.417
Wimp!

36:02.955 --> 36:04.181
Are you OK?

36:04.502 --> 36:07.063
He will be. Thanks to you.

36:08.078 --> 36:09.487
Thanks, kid.

36:10.447 --> 36:11.947
Whatevs.

36:13.501 --> 36:14.828
Frank?

36:15.870 --> 36:17.645
Time to go.

36:44.434 --> 36:45.979
Thank you, Frank...

36:46.391 --> 36:48.449
for getting us this far.

36:48.569 --> 36:50.983
You can thank Ali, he's quite a boy.

36:51.202 --> 36:52.519
Yeah, he is.

36:59.232 --> 37:01.446
You and Cat are good together...

37:05.735 --> 37:07.213
What is it?

37:07.537 --> 37:09.256
Al-Harazi.

37:20.533 --> 37:22.060
You can't outrun them.

37:22.180 --> 37:24.496
The thought has occurred to me.

37:27.019 --> 37:28.408
Everybody, get down!

37:35.999 --> 37:37.398
The border!

37:37.518 --> 37:38.652
I see it.

37:38.862 --> 37:40.591
Tell the boys to grab onto something.

37:40.600 --> 37:42.101
Grab onto something!

38:21.511 --> 38:23.524
That say danger!

38:23.546 --> 38:25.002
The mines. We're safe.

38:25.046 --> 38:27.000
As long as we stay on the road.

38:44.284 --> 38:46.179
We can't have that, can we?

39:05.826 --> 39:07.282
You the man!

39:07.590 --> 39:10.268
Never had an audience before.

39:13.158 --> 39:14.995
Al-Harazi's still behind us!

39:16.246 --> 39:18.559
He's not going away. Not without some help.

39:19.803 --> 39:21.611
Here, take the wheel.

39:21.644 --> 39:22.657
Me?

39:23.111 --> 39:24.025
Yeah.

39:25.452 --> 39:26.879
Just drive fast.

39:30.337 --> 39:31.994
You stay up front.

39:32.418 --> 39:34.328
I help, you'll see.

39:47.644 --> 39:48.910
Get me some cloths...

39:49.298 --> 39:51.266
Rags, anything.

39:54.642 --> 39:55.664
Frank.

40:11.029 --> 40:12.427
Like this.

40:16.797 --> 40:17.996
You OK?

40:48.733 --> 40:50.709
We're here!

41:05.781 --> 41:07.801
The bastard doesn't give up.

41:15.487 --> 41:16.654
Get down!

41:30.601 --> 41:32.627
Hold on to something!

42:04.267 --> 42:05.627
You are good.

42:09.533 --> 42:10.646
C'mon.

42:14.715 --> 42:17.422
_

42:47.333 --> 42:48.804
Where's Zac?

42:59.325 --> 43:01.723
- What are you doing?
- I'm looking for something.

43:03.379 --> 43:04.425
Got it?

43:04.727 --> 43:06.394
- Cat's bracelet.
- C'mon.

43:18.365 --> 43:20.165
- Frank!
- Stop!

43:22.295 --> 43:23.443
Go.

43:23.663 --> 43:25.741
Not without the package. That's you.

43:26.514 --> 43:28.119
Ali come back!

43:29.143 --> 43:31.287
Ali! Ali!

43:31.725 --> 43:34.111
_

43:34.154 --> 43:36.445
_

43:58.651 --> 44:01.139
I think we found the Angel of Zouaret.

44:04.936 --> 44:07.322
_

44:11.316 --> 44:13.585
_

44:58.536 --> 45:00.004
Do you want drink?

45:00.124 --> 45:02.499
"Do you want a drink?"

45:06.005 --> 45:07.007
Sure, kid.

45:07.051 --> 45:08.302
Give it here.

45:13.217 --> 45:14.651
I got us a car.

45:15.121 --> 45:16.884
There's a jet waiting in Ouarzazate.

45:17.213 --> 45:18.333
Thank you,

45:18.923 --> 45:20.572
but these boys still need me.

45:23.580 --> 45:25.834
You didn't think I'd
actually leave, did you?

45:28.848 --> 45:30.333
No, not really.

45:30.453 --> 45:32.104
You got me across the border, Frank.

45:32.119 --> 45:34.050
I'll make sure my father pays you.

45:34.270 --> 45:36.216
Well, I can't say it's been a pleasure...

45:38.642 --> 45:40.400
I'll see you around, Mr. Martin.

45:42.962 --> 45:45.362
Why don't you show me what
you can do with that ball?

45:51.721 --> 45:52.979
This is the part where you tell me

45:53.008 --> 45:54.450
what a terrible mistake that you made.

45:54.570 --> 45:55.690
Zac...

45:56.389 --> 45:58.738
You risked your life,
came all the way here.

45:58.761 --> 46:00.428
Why do that if you don't still love me?

46:03.523 --> 46:06.209
Because the world's a
better place with you in it.

46:09.604 --> 46:10.614
Hey...

46:12.575 --> 46:14.141
You're gonna want this back.

46:17.740 --> 46:18.903
You keep it.

46:20.650 --> 46:22.511
I don't need it anymore.

